<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-16T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-16T02:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115 China National Aviation
                            Company/62: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-16T16:00:00+09:00">September 16, 1938—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 16—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>604. Department’s 316, September 14, 2 p.m., China National Aviation
                            Corporation. Note was handed to the Foreign Office this afternoon. No
                            substantive change was made in the text authorized by the Department
                            except for incorporation in the first paragraph of our note of an
                            appropriate reference to previous correspondence.</p>
                        <p>See also our 605, September 16, 5 p.m.<note n="92" xml:id="d640fn92"><hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>